a ) respectable $372,000.=C2=A0

=E2=80=8A

Endnotes=E2=80=A6
-----------

Perhaps you saw the news this weekend that the Brooklyn Museum is cutting
staff due to a budget shortfall of $10 million. Director Anne Pasternak sai=
d ( https://www.nytimes.com/2025/02/07/arts/design/brooklyn-museum-layoffs.=
html?utm_campaign=3DWall+Power+-+SUBSCRIBERS+%282%2F9%2F25%29&utm_content=
=3DWall+Power+-+SUBSCRIBERS+%282%2F9%2F25%29&utm_medium=3Demail_action&utm_=
source=3Dcustomer.io&utm_term=3Df6c60617da42abd12a ) the deficit was caused=
 by inflation raising costs on the operating budget and the pandemic reduci=
ng attendance. I=E2=80=99ve been speaking to a number of art market insider=
s who say several galleries are having real cashflow issues. Few industry v=
eterans have seen a market
downturn as long as this one, even though there still seems to be an appeti=
te for art.=C2=A0

=C2=A0

Just to add to your anxiety, I feel compelled to point out that I read ( ht=
tps://www.washingtonpost.com/business/interactive/2025/elon-musk-doge-gover=
nment-budget-cuts-quiz/?utm_campaign=3DWall+Power+-+SUBSCRIBERS+%282%2F9%2F=
25%29&utm_content=3DWall+Power+-+SUBSCRIBERS+%282%2F9%2F25%29&utm_medium=3D=
email_action&utm_source=3Dcustomer.io&utm_term=3Df6c60617da42abd12a ) last =
week that Elon Musk claims he will cut $2 trillion from
federal spending through his scarcely legal DOGE project. (Maybe we=E2=80=
=99re supposed to apply the same =E2=80=9Cnot literally but seriously=E2=80=
=9D formula to Musk=E2=80=99s statements, but humor me here.) The comments =
caused me to do some back-of-the-envelope calculations. Federal spending is=
 23 percent of G.D.P. in the United States. That $2 trillion represents 29 =
percent of federal spending. So we can expect G.D.P. to fall in the United =
States by more than 6.67 percentage points. Just for context, the so-called=
 great
recession in the United States that followed the global financial crisis in=
 2008 and 2009 knocked 4.3 percent off G.D.P. I=E2=80=99m not saying Musk w=
ill be successful. But if he is, the already weakened art market will be se=
verely affected. Even billionaires will stop spending when the economy cont=
racts more than 6.5 percent.=C2=A0

Meanwhile, the art world has done itself no favors with the dubious success=
 of Maurizio Cattelan=E2=80=99s
Comedian. Let me be the first to remind you that I thought ( https://puck.n=
ews/can-a-banana-duct-taped-to-a-wall-save-the-art-market/?utm_campaign=3DW=
all+Power+-+SUBSCRIBERS+%282%2F9%2F25%29&utm_content=3DWall+Power+-+SUBSCRI=
BERS+%282%2F9%2F25%29&utm_medium=3Demail_action&utm_source=3Dcustomer.io&ut=
m_term=3Df6c60617da42abd12a ) a successful sale of the duct-tape-and-banana=
 artwork would be a boon for art, bringing back excitement and interest in =
conceptual work. How wrong I was.

Julie Davich shared with me this morning a link to Meta=E2=80=99s Super Bow=
l
ad ( https://youtu.be/2fyqvZ_nmO8?si=3D4NnLrpOMLfLRKoL2&utm_campaign=3DWall=
+Power+-+SUBSCRIBERS+%282%2F9%2F25%29&utm_content=3DWall+Power+-+SUBSCRIBER=
S+%282%2F9%2F25%29&utm_medium=3Demail_action&utm_source=3Dcustomer.io&utm_t=
erm=3Df6c60617da42abd12a ) promoting their Ray-Ban smart glasses. It featur=
es actors Chris Hemsworth and Chris Pratt, and a brief appearance by Kris J=
enner. In the ad, Pratt and Hemsworth wander through an art collection=E2=
=80=94supposedly Jenner=E2=80=99s home=E2=80=94asking their Meta smart glas=
ses to identify and explain art works. Central to the commercial is
Comedian=E2=80=94the $6.2 million price is mentioned prominently=E2=80=94wh=
ich Hemsworth nonchalantly snacks on. (Geddit?) Then, of course, the ad get=
s the point of the art work all wrong. (Eating the banana doesn=E2=80=99t d=
amage the work in any way.)=C2=A0

=C2=A0

I can think of nothing positive that comes from this=E2=80=94except possibl=
y for Jenner, who just
listed ( https://www.realtor.com/news/celebrity-real-estate/kris-jenner-kee=
ping-with-kardashians-house-sale-photos/?utm_campaign=3DWall+Power+-+SUBSCR=
IBERS+%282%2F9%2F25%29&utm_content=3DWall+Power+-+SUBSCRIBERS+%282%2F9%2F25=
%29&utm_medium=3Demail_action&utm_source=3Dcustomer.io&utm_term=3Df6c60617d=
a42abd12a ) the Hidden Hills house featured in the ad for $13.5 million. No=
 one thinks Jenner is a cool art collector, though it was nice to see someo=
ne did their homework and put an Urs Fischer candle self-portrait in the op=
ening. The ad only reinforces the idea that contemporary art is stupid. (By=
 the way, the Comedian (Ban) ( https://www.coingecko.com/en/coins/comedian?=
utm_campaign=3DWall+Power+-+SUBSCRIBERS+%282%2F9%2F25%29&utm_content=3DWall=
+Power+-+SUBSCRIBERS+%282%2F9%2F25%29&utm_medium=3Demail_action&utm_source=
=3Dcustomer.io&utm_term=3Df6c60617da42abd12a ) memecoin still has a $68 mil=
lion market value.)

=C2=A0

Also, it gets the rules of borrowed interest backwards: Meta=E2=80=99s glas=
ses are supposed to be cool when compared with contemporary art, but lampoo=
ning Comedian only denigrates Meta=E2=80=99s Ray-Bans themselves, which, I =
don=E2=80=99t have to tell you,
have been a flop. More to the point, the naff eat-the-banana punchline was =
already dated in 2019.

=C2=A0

Other than that, I hope you enjoy the game.

=C2=A0

